{
  "stem": "25423.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Secondly, a member of the Jewish Agency at that time, Emil Shmorak from Lvov, was a friend of my father.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was kind enough to take interest in me and introduced me to the registrar of the Hebrew University, Dr.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Posnaisky. ?] So I was admitted without any difficulty because of my documents.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But what's more important, I was given free tuition.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Shmorak arranged a small stipend for me of 20 Israeli-- or Palestinian pounds a month, which allowed me to subsist in Jerusalem and study.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not really.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You had to have very powerful connections for that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then I published my book, and I suddenly became a man of means, because I got 200 Palestinian pounds for my book.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I was much more relaxed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Difficult?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First of all, I was there at a very interesting time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was privileged to be still in the days when the old Zionist i-- idealism permeated the country.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I lived in a kibbutz for a while, and then at the Hebrew University.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was very happy here and very proud to be part of it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was a member of the Haganah, and then I graduated from the Haganah commander school-- [INAUDIBLE] commander school, which was a privilege.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was perhaps physically very hard, and maybe also emotionally hard, because I had to adapt to sabras and people with a different outlook from mine, who didn't have the horrible burden of the memories of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But by and large, if I did not insist on bringing up the Holocaust or show a deep sense of sorrow for myself, I was accepted and functioned among them reasonably well and was quite happy.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
